
                          CALL FOR PAPERS
             Twenty-Ninth Annual Asilomar Conference on
                   Signals, Systems, and Computers

Sunday-Wednesday                         October 29 - November 1,1995
Asilomar Hotel                           Pacific Grove
& Conference Grounds                     California

Before June 1, 1995 authors are invited to submit papers in the following 
general areas:

  1. Multidimensional Signal &        9. Time Frequency Representations
     Image Processing                    
  2. Linear & Nonlinear Digital      10. Analog & Digital VLSI Design
     Signal Processing
  3. Adaptive Signal Processing      11. DSP Hardware Implementation
  4. Sensor Array Processing         12. Wavelets and Filter Banks
  5. Speech Processing               13. Higher-Order Statistics
  6. Communications                  14. Video Technology
  7. Radar and Sonar                 15. Neural Networks
  8. Biomedical                      16. Others


Two copies of a 50 to 100 word abstract and an extended summary (500 to 
1000 words plus figures) should be submitted.  The extended summary will 
be evaluated for its significance and originality. Abstracts must be 
headed by the paper title, each author's name, affiliation, full address, 
telephone/fax number, e-mail address and the technical areas(s) with
number(s) from the above list, where the paper falls.  Abstracts should be 
suitable for printing in an Abstract Book which will be available at the 
Conference.  NO MORE THAN FOUR SUBMISSIONS PER CONTRIBUTOR, AS AUTHOR OR 
CO-AUTHOR, ARE ALLOWED.  ALL SUBMISSIONS MUST BE RECEIVED BY JUNE 1, 1995.  
Notifications of acceptance will be mailed by the end of July 1995, and 
author kits will be sent by mid September 1995.  Full papers will be due 
at the Conference, and published in the spring of 1996.  ALL TECHNICAL
QUESTIONS SHOULD BE DIRECTED TO THE TECHNICAL PROGRAM CHAIRMAN, DR. MICHAEL 
A. SODERSTRAND at dsplab@ece.ucdavis.edu, phone (916) 752-2669, fax (916) 
752-8428.

Regular mail submissions should be sent to:

     Asilomar Conference Technical Program Chairman
     c/o ECE Department, Code EC
     Naval Postgraduate School
     833 Dyer Rd., Room 437
     Monterey, CA 93943-5121



ADDITIONAL INSTRUCTIONS:

1. REGULAR MAIL SUBMISSIONS:
In addition to the material described above, authors should include with their submission a separate page containing a camera ready copy of the abstract headed by the paper title, and each author's name and affiliation.  The typeface must be clear and legible, and all information on this page must fit within a 2.5" high by 6.5" wide area for printing in the Abstract book.


2.ELECTRONIC SUBMISSIONS:
Only one copy of the material need to be e-mailed to asilomar@ece.nps.navy.mil .  Only plain text format will be accepted.


FTP SITE INFORMATION:  Registration and Advance Program Information will 
be available after 7/15/95 at the anonymous ftp site ftp.nps.navy.mil in 
directory /pub/ece/asilomar . 


